    "summary": "About me\nI am a seasoned, highly driven finance professional, with 16 years of progressive experience. Including 10 years of managerial experience, gained at KPMG, Xella Group and Fabory Group. Currently holding a Group Finance Director position at Fabory Group. \n\nI have extensive finance, accounting and controlling experience. Added with strong business acumen and a natural commercial interest. I use a coaching management style, creating high performance and engaged teams. Possessing strong leadership and stakeholder management skills. Being a positive and energetic person and a goal-oriented team player. Pro-active and hands-on to get things done, realize on plan and drive improvements. Leveraging of strong analytic, strategic and people management skills. \n\nAbout Fabory\nFabory is a leading specialist supplier of fasteners and fastener related products with a pan-European and China presence. Fabory sources a broad assortment of high quality and mission-critical fasteners from suppliers worldwide and distributes to over 65,000 customers throughout Europe and Asia. Its clients' base ranks from Blue-chip customers to SME across various end markets, including machine building, electrical appliances, automotive and construction. \n\nWith more than 400.000 products, market knowledge and expertise in supply chain solutions, we can provide peace of mind for our partners and customers from A to Z. Fabory's head office is in Tilburg, and its international operations cover 10 European countries. With over 1,000 employees, we operate in 10 different branches and five distributions centers.",
